    <string name="help_storage_title">Where are files saved?</string>
    <string name="help_storage_description">Photos and reports are saved in the following location on your device:

Internal storage: DCIM/warehouse/

For Android 10+ devices, files are saved to:
Android/data/com.warehouse.camera/files/Pictures/warehouse/

You can transfer these files to your computer using a USB cable or view them directly in the File Structure browser within the app.</string>
    <string name="help_howto_title">How to use the app</string>
    <string name="help_howto_description">1. Create or select a reception
2. Enter manufacturer code (4 digits) and select date
3. Choose defect category (1-3 based on severity)
4. Enter article information and scan barcode if needed
5. Take damage photos and barcode photos with appropriate color marking
6. Save the item
7. Add more items if needed
8. View your photos in the gallery
9. Complete documentation when finished</string>
